Consider this SystemVerilog file:

    module top(...);
      input clk;
      input [7:0] data;
      input ack;

      always @(posedge clk)
        if (ack) begin
          assert(data != 8'h0a);
        end
    endmodule

Before this commit, the span for the assert was:

        if (ack) begin>
          assert(data != 8'h0a)<;

After this commit, the span for the assert is:

        if (ack) begin
          >assert(data != 8'h0a)<;

This helps editor integrations that only look at the beginning of the span.
